Pre-Game Insights: The Atlas Lions take on The Taifa Stars in their first clash of the AFCON 2023.
Morocco have a long history in African football and their World Cup performances stand for it.
Tanzania are well-known for their love of football and hopes to demonstrate talent and resiliency.
Kick-off is scheduled for Wednesday, 17th January 2024, 5:00 PM GMT; 10:30 PM IST at Stade de San Pédro.
Morocco's recent form in all competitions is W-D-W-W-W.
Tanzania's recent form in all competitions is D-D-W-L-L.
Youssef En-Nesyri is a well-known Moroccan player who excels at scoring goals and in aerial situations.
Charles M’Mombwa is a key player for Tanzania, known for his versatility and energy on the pitch.
This is the opening match for both teams in Group F of the AFCON 2023.
There have been three competitions between the Moroccan and Tanzanian teams since 2013, with Morocco winning two of those matches.
Noussair Mazraoui may not feature in this game of AFCON.
El Kaabi and Tissoudali are available to fill in as strikers for Morocco if necessary.
Haji Mnoga, Tarryn Allarakhia, and Anthony Ben Starkie are interested to start for Tanzania.
Predicted lineup for Morocco (4-4-2): Bono; Hakimi, Aguerd, Saïss, Mazraoui; Ounahi, Amrabat, Ziyech, Harit; El Khannouss, En-Nesyri.
Predicted lineup for Tanzania (4-3-3): Manula; Dickson, Nondo, Mnoga, Miroshi; Msuva, Hamad, Bajana; Samatta, M’Mombwa, Salum.
